			    STPJS 312</div>
  <p class="std">Peter<span class="footRef">1</span> and Stephen testify<span class="footRef">2</span> that they saw the Son of Man standing on the right hand of God.<span class="footRef">3</span>
  Any person that had seen the heavens opened<span class="footRef">4</span> knows that there are three personages in the heavens
  who hold the keys of power, and one presides over all.</p>
  <p class="std">If any man attempts to refute<span class="footRef">5</span> what I am about to say, after I have made it plain, let him
  beware.<span class="footRef">6</span></p>
  <div class="topic">The Son Does What the Father Did</div>
  <p class="std">As the Father hath power in Himself, so hath the Son power in Himself,<span class="footRef">7</span> to lay down His life
  and take it again,<span class="footRef">8</span> so He has a body of His own. The Son doeth what He hath seen the Father do:<span class="footRef">9</span>
  then the Father hath some day laid down His life and taken it again;<span class="footRef">10</span> so He has a body of His own;<span class="footRef">11</span>
  each one will be in His own body; and yet the sectarian world believe the body of the Son is
  identical with the Father&rsquo;s.</p>
  <p class="std">Gods have an ascendency over the angels, who are ministering servants.<span class="footRef">12</span> In the resurrection,
  some are raised to be angels, others are raised to become Gods.<span class="footRef">13</span></p>
  <p class="std">These things are revealed in the most holy places in a Temple<span class="footRef">14</span> prepared for that purpose. Many
  of the sects cry out, &ldquo;Oh, I have the testimony of Jesus; I have the spirit of God; but away with Joe
  Smith; he says he is a prophet; but there are to be no prophets or revelators in the last days.&rdquo; Stop,
  sir! The Revelator says that the testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy;<span class="footRef">15</span> so by your own mouth
  you are condemned.<span class="footRef">16</span> But to the text. Why gather the people together in this place? For the same
  purpose that Jesus wanted to gather the Jews<span class="footRef">17</span>&mdash;to receive the ordinances, the blessings, and glories
  that God has in store for His Saints.<span class="footRef">18</span></p>
  <p class="std">I will now ask this assembly and all the Saints if you will now build this house<span class="footRef">19</span> and receive the
  ordinances and blessings which God has in store for you;<span class="footRef">20</span> or will you not build unto the Lord this
  house, and let Him pass by and bestow these blessings<span class="footRef">21</span> upon another people?<span class="footRef">22</span> I pause for a reply.
  (June 11, 1843.) DHC 5:423–427.</p>
  <div class="topic">The Cause of the Prophet&rsquo;s Success&mdash;Love for His Fellow-Man</div>
  <p class="std">Joseph remarked that all was well between him and the heavens;<span class="footRef">23</span> that he had no enmity against
